entries.meaning: A subordinate delegate, or one with inferior powers.

verbs.description: subdelegate (third-person singular simple present subdelegates, present participle subdelegating, simple past and past participle subdelegated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To delegate (a task already delegated to oneself) to somebody else.
examples: To subdelegate a determinate priest to assist at a specified marriage of those subjects of the Military Vicar who have been placed under your personal charge, excluding entirely, however, the power of again subdelegating.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To appoint as a subdelegate or subordinate.
